<h3>Public Transit Reality</h3>
<div class="consequence-text"><p>You commit to using public transportation. It's the most affordable option to get you to work.</p><p>The bus and train system can get you close to the work sites, though not exactly where you need to be. You'll still have to walk the last bit, carrying your tools with you.</p><p>It's cheaper than the alternatives, but there are risks. For example, the Chicago Police Department might question people carrying large bags or work equipment.</p></div>
<hr>
<div class="consequence-text"><p>Now you need to decide how you'll structure your work once you get to the job areas:</p></div>
